Sympy
=====

Computer algebra system (CAS) in python

http://code.google.com/p/sympy/


Ondrej Certik <ondrej@certik.cz>

License: GNU General Public License 2.0
covers all the files in the sympy repository.



0. Download
-----------

svn checkout http://sympy.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ sympy


1. Documentation
---------------

http://code.google.com/p/sympy/wiki/Documentation

Examples are at:

http://code.google.com/p/sympy/wiki/Examples

Other documentation is in sym/__init__.py and in a form of comments in the
source code, plus some information is at
http://code.google.com/p/sympy/.

See also the "todo" file for things which are still missing.

2. Usage
--------

From this directory, start python and:
>>> import sym
>>> x=sym.symbol("x")
>>> e=1/sym.cos(x)
>>> print e.series(x,10)
1+1/2*x^2+5/24*x^4+61/720*x^6+277/8064*x^8+50521/3628800*x^10

3. Tests
--------

to execute tests, run

py.test

in the current directory.  You may need to install py.test.

4. How to install py.test
-------------------------

Execute in your home directory:

svn co http://codespeak.net/svn/py/dist py-dist

This will create a "py-dist" directory in you home dir. Add this line to
.bashrc:

eval `python ~/py-dist/py/env.py`

Now you can call "py.test" from anywhere.
